From the manufacturer

Pokémon TCG: Scarlet & Violet—151 Ultra-Premium Collection

Mythical Treasures Await!

The Mythical Pokémon Mew holds many secrets of the Pokémon world, and usually only the luckiest of Trainers encounter it. But now you can add it to your own Pokédex along with even more Kanto Pokémon inside a bounty of booster packs from the Scarlet & Violet—151 expansion! Mew ex appears here as both playable and collectible metal cards, and you’ll also find a beautifully illustrated promo card featuring Mewtwo, a durable playmat and deck box, and more.

The Pokémon TCG: Scarlet & Violet—151 Ultra-Premium Collection includes:

  • 1 etched foil promo card featuring Mew ex
  • 1 full-art foil promo card featuring Mewtwo
  • 1 etched metal card featuring Mew ex
  • 1 playmat
  • 1 deck box
  • 1 metallic coin featuring Mew
  • 6 damage-counter dice
  • 2 plastic condition markers
  • 16 booster packs from Pokémon TCG: Scarlet & Violet—151
  • A code card for Pokémon TCG Live

        4.0 out of 5 stars Lower quality than expected but still great
        Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
        Verified Purchase
        The box itself was a bit damaged and was loosely sealed in plastic wrap. Some of the pieces inside was also flipped backwards which was a bit sketchy but all in all, it was fun to open. Our pulls weren’t the best but it’s always hit or miss with boxes like this. The quality of the cards were nice but the coins and dice were below par. These are even worse quality than the plastic coins that the older packs came with so sadly quality is declining. I was hoping a box like this (like the Charizard box) would’ve had metal coins and dice but it didn’t bother me too much. I was confused though why they don’t include the big dice anymore. The mat that it came with was beautiful quality though and mostly made up for the cheap coins. The lack of card sleeves is also a bit of a bummer but I like the cool box it comes with. I’ll just find clear sleeves later for it.

        All in all, I don’t think it was worth the price I paid, especially since one can get more and better things from the charizard box like this one that’s about the same price, but it was still fun to open and I’m excited to begin my collection of the new gen cards.

        RJ
        3.0 out of 5 stars 151 Ultra Premium Collection - I Like it, but I'm disappointed in the production quality control
        Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2023
        Verified Purchase
        At the time of review I've opened 2 of the Ultra Premium Collections, current price is $119, both were ordered through Amazon, the first came from a third-party seller, the second came from Amazon; both arrived in good condition and were packaged well. The one shipped from Amazon arrived in slightly better condition without any crushed box corners. All items were accounted for in both boxes, everything was properly sealed and appears to be authentic.

        Each collection includes 16 booster packs, 2 promo cards, 1 promo metal card, a playmat, and other various game play items. The promo cards were packaged nicely and were protected in the box. Based on the current price and giving a rough value of $40 for the promotional items, and $80 for the 16 packs of cards, this gives an approximate value of $5 per booster pack.

        The following is from the second box opened: of the 16 packs: we received 4 full art cards, including a golden energy card, two ex cards, four holographic energy cards, and a good number of other holographic cards and reverse holographic cards.

        The following is based on many packs opened from the 151 set and not just Premium Collection:
        Overall, I like the 151 set and was excited to collect it. However, I am very disappointed in the quality control in the production of the cards. Many of the cards have production marks and divots. The centering of the Tangela full art card was awful, but worst of all was the coloring in comparison with the Japanese version of the same card. The Mew EX card was so bad in comparison that I was worried that I didn't receive an authentic card, and it wasn't until I got a second that I was able to confirm that it was just the low-quality printing from the manufacture that made the card look so dull, lackluster, and lacking in fine detail. I've included a picture with side-by-side cards of the US and Japanese version for comparison to show the color differences.

        I wish I could give this set more stars but with the low level of quality control I just can't, and I hope this is corrected in future sets.
